http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/Elephants-live-it-up-at-Vandalur/article13995731.ece

The calves are beneficiaries of the rejuvenation camp for elephants that is in progress at the Arignar Anna Zoological Park in Vandalur.At the camp, which will be on till February 28, three calves – Urigam (6), Giri (5) and Asokan (5) – are provided with a generous supply of sumptuous food, which includes green gram and jaggery. This apart, they are provided with large quantities of regular food, including rice, ragi, fruits, coconuts and sugarcane.Protein supplementsAccording to a press release, they will also be given vitamin and protein supplements. They will be given shower baths twice a day, and doctors will conduct regular check-ups.Visitors will also be allowed to see the calves in the camp. In the 2014-15 season, the camp began in December, but this time the officials had to postpone it by a month due unprecedented rains during December, 2015.